   (BUTTON) Masquer les détails
   Abstract : We investigate the shifts associated with natural codings of
   linear in-volutions. We deduce from the geometric representation of
   linear invo-lutions as Poincaré maps of measured foliations a suitable
   definition of return words which yields that the set of return words to
   a given word is a symmetric basis of the free group on the underlying
   alphabet A. The set of return words with respect to a subgroup of
   finite index G of the free group on A is also proved to be a symmetric
   basis of G.
   Type de document :
   Article dans une revue
   Domaine :

   Mathématiques [math]
   Informatique [cs]

