   Rewriting Higher-Order Stack Trees
   Systèmes de réécriture d’arbres de piles
   Vincent Penelle ^1, * (BUTTON) Détails
   * Auteur correspondant
   1 LIGM - Laboratoire d'Informatique Gaspard-Monge

       Vincent Penelle ^1 AuthorId : 1129463
     Auteur correspondant

   1 LIGM - Laboratoire d'Informatique Gaspard-Monge (Université de
   Paris-Est Marne-la-Vallée, Cité Descartes, Bâtiment Copernic, 5 bd
   Descartes, 77454 Marne-la-Vallée Cedex 2 - France) StructId : 3210
     * UPEM - Université Paris-Est Marne-la-Vallée (5 boulevard Descartes
       - Champs-sur-Marne - 77454 Marne-la-Vallée Cedex 2 - France)
       StructId : 301243
     * ENPC - École des Ponts ParisTech (École des Ponts ParisTech 6-8
       avenue Blaise-Pascal Cité Descartes 77455 Champs-sur-Marne
       Marne-la-Vallée cedex 2 - France) StructId : 301545
     * ESIEE Paris (2 boulevard Blaise Pascal Cité Descartes BP 99 93162
       Noisy-le-Grand Cedex - France) StructId : 302035
     * Fédération de Recherche Bézout (France) StructId : 302085
     * CNRS - Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique : UMR8049
       (France) StructId : 441569

   (BUTTON) Masquer les détails
   Abstract : Higher-order pushdown systems and ground tree rewriting
   systems can be seen as extensions of suffix word rewriting systems.
   Both classes generate infinite graphs with interesting logical
   properties. In-deed, the model-checking problem for monadic second
   order logic (re-spectively first order logic with a reachability
   predicate) is decidable on such graphs. We unify both models by
   introducing the notion of stack trees, trees whose nodes are labelled
   by higher-order stacks, and define the corresponding class of
   higher-order ground tree rewriting systems. We show that these graphs
   retain the decidability properties of ground tree rewriting graphs
   while generalising the pushdown hierarchy of graphs.
   Keywords : stack trees
   Type de document :
   Communication dans un congrès
   Domaine :

   Informatique [cs] / Théorie et langage formel [cs.FL]

